



Sir
Watertown [Mass.] Octor 4th 1775



In the Brigantine Dolphin lately carried into Gloucester, the two Women accompanying this were Passengers1There names are Margaret Roberts & Mary KnapThey say they have Husbands belonging to the 59th Regt of Genl Gages ArmyAnd are desirous of seeing themI am therefore directed by the
[94]
Board, to recommend to your Exy to permit them and 2 Children, to pass your Lines, in order to their proceeding into Boston.

By order of the Council
P. Morton Dpy secry

